During the course deals with the following topics:
- the meaning and criteria of professionalism;
- professional attitude and identity;
- professional guidance, reflecting it;
- professional ethics of teacher and youth worker;
- quality in youth work, evaluation of it.Objectives/eesmärkid:  - To associate the knowledge acquired from the Community Education and Hobby Activity curriculum with professionalism; - To support understanding the principles of developing professional learning and development activities.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has completed the course -understands the importance of professional skills and knowledge in education and youth work; -can determine his/her own needs and possibilities for professional development; -knows the requirements for the professional ethics of teacher and youth worker;  -values the creative approach and alternative solutions in developing his/her own professional skills.
